This paper deals with optimization algorithms for partitioning graphs with supply and demand, which is a problem that can be applied to electrical distribution systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which deals with combinatorial optimization problems. The paper also uses ant colony optimization, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves artificial intelligence techniques, which could place it in the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with system optimization, which could place it in the category of cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) due to its focus on optimization of interconnected microgrids.
